comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-07T06:50:35.049Z",maintainer-agent,"Subsystem-map addition proposed: pm-uwfs (context usage feedback signal) supplies the one mechanism this ADR's seven-subsystem map omits — memory strengthening through recall (retrieval-practice effect). If this ADR is accepted, add it as the eighth mapping: served-then-acted-on outcomes -> usage-affinity scoring input in pm-4k6b, with the existing graceful-forgetting decay as the complementary weakening term. Exploration/anti-lock-in guard is stated in pm-uwfs acceptance criteria."
notes[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-07T07:27:15.697Z",maintainer-agent,"Planning pass 2026-07-07: two candidate subsystems to complete the human-memory mapping (file as items only on ADR acceptance):\n(1) Prospective memory — remembering to act in the future. Primitives exist (Reminder/Event types, start_at/end_at, deadline signal in pm-3hps) but are not yet composed: due/imminent scheduled items should surface in context/next automatically when temporally relevant, without the agent polling a calendar. Depends on pm-x1g5 (get omits schedule facet) being fixed first.\n(2) Metacognition — knowing what you do not know. The confidence metadata field should modulate recall, not just describe items: low-confidence decisions/learnings get resurfaced for revalidation when their subject matter re-enters the working set (semantic-match trigger), and a bounded \"known unknowns\" projection lists load-bearing low-confidence context. Complements pm-uwfs (retrieval practice strengthens; metacognition flags what needs re-checking)."
  "2026-07-07T14:28:32.662Z",maintainer-agent,"Planning pass 2026-07-07 (follow-up): third candidate subsystem to complete the human-memory mapping (same convention — file as an item only on ADR acceptance):\n(3) Interference & belief revision — human memory resolves contradictions between new and old knowledge instead of serving both. pm mapping, two halves: (a) write-time conflict advisory — when a new learning/decision is semantically near-identical to an existing one but points the other way, surface the older entry before the write lands (extends the pm-4ri6 create-time near-duplicate advisory from items to knowledge entries; same hybrid-similarity machinery, different corpus); (b) supersedence as a first-class relation — a decision/learning can record supersedes/superseded_by so context assembly serves the current belief and demotes (never deletes) the superseded one; the full trail stays replayable via immutable history. Complements #10 metacognition: conflict detection flags WHAT to revalidate, confidence modulation decides WHEN. ADR-practice precedent: superseded status is standard for ADR lifecycles and pm-m2u1 (living ADR log) currently has no supersedence edge."
  "2026-07-07T14:44:15.568Z",maintainer-agent,"Planning pass 2026-07-07 (second follow-up): fourth candidate subsystem for the human-memory mapping (same convention — file as an item only on ADR acceptance):\n(4) Novelty detection / orienting response — human attention is drawn preferentially to what CHANGED since it last looked; a returning agent's highest-value context is the delta it has not yet seen. pm mapping: derive a per-author watermark from the agent's own last authored history entry (zero new state — pure derivation from the immutable episodic streams), then treat changed-by-OTHERS-since-watermark as a salience signal in context/next assembly, with the delta summarized in bounded tokens (\"catching up\" projection). Distinct from pm-4k6b author affinity (affinity ranks what I touched; novelty surfaces what I have NOT seen change) and strictly beyond closed pm-ankr/pm-y138 (those shipped manual --updated-since windows; here the system derives the watermark itself, so the agent never has to remember its own last visit). Composes episodic memory (history streams) into working-memory assembly; complements #1 prospective memory (time-triggered) with change-triggered attention. Small-workspace neutral: with one author and no interleaved writers the delta is empty and the signal is silent."
body: "## Context\nThe product philosophy is \"project management = context management\": the tracker must let an agent rebuild optimal working context at any moment, at any workspace scale. The building blocks exist as separate backlog items — pm-4k6b relevance engine, pm-5qmm memory tiers, pm-atfm quality harness, pm-hib1 point-in-time reads, pm focus, learnings/decisions, append-only history streams — but no recorded decision states the unifying model they compose into. The stated long-term goal (agents building near-human context continuity from pm alone) needs an explicit architecture so future context features strengthen one coherent system instead of accreting ad-hoc signals.\n\n## Proposal\nModel agent context assembly on the architecture of human memory. Each subsystem maps to a pm primitive that already exists or is on the roadmap:\n\n- **Working memory (attention):** pm focus + token-budgeted context/next assembly (pm-4k6b) — the small, high-relevance active set an agent holds \"in mind\".\n- **Episodic memory:** per-item append-only history streams + point-in-time reads (pm-hib1) — what happened, when, by whom; immutable and replayable.\n- **Semantic memory:** learnings, decisions/ADRs, and the knowledge-density ranking signal (pm-4k6b) — distilled facts that outlive the episodes that produced them.\n- **Procedural memory:** plans, templates, profiles, schema — how this workspace does things.\n- **Consolidation:** derived closed-epoch rollups (pm-5qmm) + history-compact checkpoints — episodic detail summarizes into semantic form as it ages, in bounded tokens.\n- **Associative recall:** dependency-graph proximity + hybrid semantic retrieval (pm-4k6b) — related context surfaces by association with the focus item, not by enumeration.\n- **Graceful forgetting:** relevance decay and projection degradation under a token budget — never deletion. Under the immutable-history invariant, \"forgotten\" only means \"not loaded\"; total recall stays possible via restore, point-in-time reads, and attestation (pm-3z0k).\n\n## Decision drivers\n- One mental model: every new context feature must name which memory subsystem it extends, keeping the engine coherent as it grows.\n- Spectrum invariance: the same architecture serves a 3-item minutes-old scratch workspace (pm-z436) and a million-item decades-spanning one (pm-g2zz); only budgets and consolidation depth change.\n- SDK-first (ADR pm-muhw): every subsystem is a public SDK primitive; CLI and MCP are presentation layers.\n- Explainability: recall must be auditable (per-signal score breakdown in pm-4k6b), never oracle-like.\n\n## Consequences (if accepted)\n- pm-4k6b, pm-5qmm, and pm-atfm acceptance criteria reference their subsystem role; pm-atfm gains continuity (\"returning agent\") scenario classes.\n- Docs gain a context-architecture page tying the philosophy to the concrete primitives (task to be filed on acceptance).\n- The returning-agent continuity story becomes the end-to-end acceptance narrative for the composed system.\n\nStatus: proposed."
